t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-field-group elementor-column elementor-field-type-submit elementor-col-100 e-form__buttons\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<button class=\"elementor-button elementor-size-sm\" type=\"submit\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"elementor-button-content-wrapper\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"elementor-button-text\">Send<\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/button>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/form>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-2eb224b elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"2eb224b\" data-element_type=\"section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-0049cec\" data-id=\"0049cec\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-459c6cd elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"459c6cd\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-large\">Where do smoky brown cockroaches live?<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-3d9378f elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"3d9378f\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Smoky brown cockroaches thrive in warm and humid environments and live in various locations, such as mulch beds, tree holes, and attics. These cockroaches primarily live outdoors but can migrate indoors during periods of drought or to seek shelter from extreme temperatures.<\/p>\n<p>Smoky brown cockroaches often dwell on roofs or sewers, where they feed on decaying organic matter. They are known for their ability to survive harsh conditions and can even withstand exposure to certain insecticides. Due to their adaptability and resilience, these cockroaches have become a major pest problem for homeowners and businesses.<\/p>\n<p>Despite being primarily an outdoor species, smoky brown cockroaches can enter homes through small cracks or openings around windows and doors. Infestations are typically identified by droppings or shed skins near food sources such as kitchens or pantries. Effective control measures include sealing building entry points and regularly cleaning areas where food is prepared or stored.<\/p>\n<p>Protect your home from smoky brown and&nbsp;<a href=\"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wood-cockroaches\/\" target=\"_blank\"><b><u>Wood cockroach<\/u><\/b><\/a>&nbsp;infestations with our proven cockroach control methods, ensuring a cockroach-free and comfortable environment.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-d1dbe55 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"d1dbe55\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-large\">Diet: What do smoky brown cockroaches eat?<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-b3d0ceb elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"b3d0ceb\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Smoky Brown Cockroaches belong to the pest family known for their resilient nature, and they have survived in a wide range of environments. This has made them infamous creatures for homeowners across the globe. One question when discussing these pests is, what exactly do they eat? Interestingly, smoky brown cockroaches are omnivores and can consume almost anything organic.<\/p><p>Their diet primarily consists of plant matter, like decaying leaves and wood chips, but they also feed on other insects and dead animals. Their scavenging nature means that they will feast on whatever is available to them, including pet food left outside or any human food left unattended in the kitchen. They have even been found to eat cardboard boxes, wallpaper paste and book bindings.<\/p><p>The ability of smoky brown cockroaches to digest rigid material makes them an asset in our ecosystem as it allows for the easy decomposition of organic matter; however, this trait also poses a threat when they invade homes as their appetite knows no bounds and can lead to severe property damage if not dealt with promptly by professionals.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-ccd2ba2 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"ccd2ba2\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-large\">Behavior: How do smoky brown cockroaches behave?<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-8e5275e elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"8e5275e\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Smoky brown cockroaches are a common household pest that can be found living in warm and humid environments. These cockroaches have a distinctive smoky-brown color and are known for their fast movements, making it difficult to catch them. They tend to fly toward light sources, making it easy for homeowners to spot them at night.<\/p><p>Furthermore, smoky brown cockroaches are omnivorous and will feed on almost anything they can find. They have been known to eat plants, garbage, feces, dead animals, and even other smaller insects. This diet allows them to thrive in various environments as they do not require specific food sources.<\/p><p>Lastly, smoky brown cockroaches prefer outdoor habitats but will occasionally venture indoors in search of food or shelter. Once inside a home or building structure, they tend to hide in dark and damp areas such as basements or crawl spaces. Homeowners must keep their homes clean and moisture-free to discourage these pests from infesting their living spaces.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-5730cb9 elementor-section-full_width elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"5730cb9\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;,&quot;background_background&quot;:&quot;classic&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-33 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-ca88c37\" data-id=\"ca88c37\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-33 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-e664faf\" data-id=\"e664faf\" data-element_type=\"column\" data-settings=\"{&quot;background_background&quot;:&quot;classic&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-d32203f elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"d32203f\" data-elemen